Name: Attack Order
Description: Attack Order is a Critical Hit on 18+

Name: Fell Stinger
Description: If the user successfully knocks out a target with Fell Stinger, raise their Attack by 2 Combat Stages.

Name: Bug Bite
Description: If the target has a stored Digestion Buff or has traded in a Digestion Buff this Scene, the user may gain the effects of the Digestion Buff. This does not count towards the usual limit on the user’s Digestion Buffs.

Name: Fury Cutter
Description: If Fury Cutter is used successfully and consecutively on the same target, the Damage Base is increased by +4 to a maximum of 16. For example, the first hit would have a DB of 4; the second hit a DB of 8; the third hit a DB of 12; the fourth and further hits a DB of 16. If Fury Cuter misses or fails to damage its target, its Damage Base resets.

Name: Bug Buzz
Description: Bug Buzz lowers the Special Defense of all targets on 19+.

Name: Heal Order
Description: The user regains Hit Points equal to half of its full Hit Point value.

Name: Defend Order
Description: Raise the user’s Defense and Special Defense 1 Combat Stage each.

Name: Infestation
Description: The target is put in a Vortex.

Name: Powder
Description: The target is dusted with a Coat of flammable powder. If it uses a damaging Fire-Type attack, the attack is negated and instad creates a Blast 3 centered on itself as the powder explodes, and the Coat is removed. All targets within the Blast take damage equal to what the user of the Fire-Type attack would roll for the damage of their attack. This damage is Typeless or Fire-Type, whichever would be more effective.

Name: Leech Life
Description: After the target takes damage, the user gains Hit Points equal to half of the damage they dealt to the target.

Name: Quiver Dance
Description: Raise the user’s Special Attack, Special Defense, and Speed by +1 Combat Stage each.

Name: Megahorn
Description: The target is pushed 1 Meter.

Name: Rage Powder
Description: All targets hit by Rage Powder are Enraged. While enraged, they must shift to target the user when using a Move or Attack if the user is within reach. If the user is Fainted or Switched out, all targets hit by Rage Powder are cured of rage.

Name: Signal Beam
Description: Signal Beam confuses the target on 19+.

Name: Sticky Web
Description: Set 8 square meters of Sticky Web hazards within your range, all 8 meters must be adjacent with at least one other space of Sticky Web. Sticky Web causes Terrain to become Slow Terrain, and a foe that runs into the hazard has its Speed lowered by one stage, and they become Slowed until the end of their next turn. Flyingtype Pokémon and Pokémon and Trainers with Levitate are not affected by Sticky Web. Bug-type Pokémon may move over Sticky Web harmlessly, destroying the Hazards as they do so.

Name: Silver Wind
Description: On 19+, the user has each of its stats raised by +1 Combat Stage.

Name: String Shot
Description: Targets have their Speed CS lowered by -1. If this lowers their Speed CS to -6, or if their Speed CS was already at -6, the target is instead Stuck.

Name: Spider Web
Description: Spider Web cannot miss. The target is Stuck and Trapped. If the user is freed of the Stuck condition, they are freed of Trapped as well.

Name: Struggle Bug
Description: On hit, lowers the target’s Special Attack by -1 CS.

Name: Steamroller
Description: Steamroller Flinches the target on 15+. If the target is Small, Steamroller deals an additional +5 Damage.

Name: Tail Glow
Description: Raise the user’s Special Attack 3 Combat Stages.

Name: Twineedle
Description: Twineedle Poisons the target on an Accuracy Check of 18+

Name: U-Turn
Description: If U-Turn successfully hits its target, the user deals damage and then immediately is returned to its Poké Ball in the same turn. A New Pokémon may immediately be sent out. Using U-Turn lets a Trapped user be recalled.

Name: Assurance
Description: When you hit with Assurance, if Assurance’s target has already been damaged by a Move on the same round Assurance is being used, Assurance has a Damage Base of 12 (3d12+10 / 30) instead. This effect may trigger only once per Scene per Target.

Name: Crunch
Description: Crunch lowers the target’s Defense 1 Combat Stage on 17+

Name: Dark Pulse
Description: Dark Pulse Flinches the target on 17+

Name: Beat Up
Description: The user and up to two allies adjacent to the target may each make a Struggle Attack against the target. These Struggle Attacks hit for Dark-Type Damage instead of their usual Type. Beat Up may trigger Pack Hunt only once, no matter the number of attacks.

Name: Dark Void
Description: The target falls Asleep. Once per scene, Dark Void may be used as if its range were “Burst 5, Friendly” instead.

Name: Bite
Description: Bite Flinches the target on 15+.

Name: Embargo
Description: The target cannot use or benefit from held items for the remainder of the encounter. Embargo may only affect one target at a time; if Embargo is used on a new target, the previous target is freed from the effect.

Name: Fake Tears
Description: Lower the target’s Special Defense 2 Combat Stages.

Name: Foul Play
Description: The target reveals its Attack stat. When calculating damage, add the target’s Attack stat instead of the user’s Attack stat.

Name: Feint Attack
Description: Feint Attack cannot miss.

Name: Hone Claws
Description: The user’s Accuracy is raised by +1, and the user gains +1 Attack Combat Stage.

Name: Flatter
Description: The target’s Special Attack is raised by +1 Combat Stage. Flatter Confuses the target.

Name: Knock Off
Description: Choose one of the target’s Held Items or Accessory Slot Items. It is knocked to the ground.

Name: Fling
Description: The user throws a held item, determining the effect of Fling.

Name: Memento
Description:
Memento may be used as a Free Action when the user becomes Fainted. Memento’s target has each of
their stats lowered by -2 CS.

Name: Nasty Plot
Description: Raise the user’s Special Attack 2 Combat Stages.

Name: Payback
Description: If the target hit the user with a Damaging Move on the previous turn, Payback has a Damage Base of 10 (3d8+10 / 24) instead.

Name: Night Daze
Description: Night Daze lowers the target’s Accuracy by -1 on 13+.

Name: Punishment
Description: Punishment’s Damage Base is raised by +1 for each positive Combat Stage the target has, to a maximum of DB 12.

Name: Night Slash
Description: Night Slash is a Critical Hit on 18+

Name: Pursuit
Description: If the foe is fleeing or being switched out, Pursuit may be used as an Interrupt, targeting the triggering foe. When used as an Interrupt, Pursuit grants the user a +5 bonus to all Movement Speeds, and has a Damage Base of 8 (2d8+10 / 19).

Name: Parting Shot
Description: If Parting Shot successfully hits, the target’s Attack and Special Attack stats are lowered by one Combat Stage and the user is immediately recalled in the same turn. A new Pokémon may immediately be sent out. Using Parting Shot lets a Trapped user be recalled.

Name: Quash
Description: Quash changes the target’s Initiative to 0 for the remainder of the round.

Name: Snarl
Description: All Legal Targets have their Special Attack lowered 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Taunt
Description: The target becomes Enraged.

Name: Thief
Description: Thief takes the target’s Held Item or Accessory Slot Item and attaches it to Thief ’s user, if the user is not holding anything.

Name: Snatch
Description: If the target uses a Self-Targeting Move, you may use Snatch. You gain the benefits of the Self-Targeting Move instead of the target.

Name: Topsy-Turvy
Description: The target’s Combat Stages are inverted; +1 Stage becomes -1 Stage, -3 Stages becomes +3 Stages, etc.

Name: Sucker Punch
Description: If an adjacent foe targets the user with a Damaging Attack, Sucker Punch may be used as an Interrupt Move against the triggering foe.

Name: Torment
Description: The target becomes Suppressed.

Name: Switcheroo
Description: The user and the target exchange Held Items or Accessory Slot Items.

Name: Draco Meteor
Description: Lower the user’s Special Attack 2 Combat Stages after damage.

Name: Dragon Rage
Description: If it hits, Dragon Rage causes the target to lose 15 Hit Points. Dragon Rage is Special and interacts with other moves and effects as such (Special Evasion may be applied to avoid it, Mirror Coat can reflect it, etc.).

Name: Dragon Claw
Description: None

Name: Dragon Rush
Description: The target is Pushed 3 meters. Dragon Rush Flinches the target on 17+.

Name: Dragon Dance
Description: Raise the user’s Attack 1 Combat Stage and raise the user’s Speed 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Dragon Tail
Description: The target is Pushed 6 meters minus their Weight Class. On a roll of 15+, the target is also Tripped.

Name: Dragon Pulse
Description: None

Name: Dragon Breath
Description: Dragon Breath Paralyzes the Target on 15+.

Name: Dual Chop
Description: None

Name: Twister
Description: Small or Medium targets in the central square of the blast are not hit. Twister Flinches the target on 18-20 during Accuracy Check. Any Pokémon Airborne as a result of Fly or Sky Drop above the Blast are hit, ignoring range, and Twister has a Damage Base of 8 against those targets instead.

Name: Outrage
Description: After damage is dealt, the user becomes Enraged and Confused.

Name: Roar of Time
Description: All legal targets are Slowed, even if the attack misses.

Name: Special Rend
Description: Rend is a Critical Hit on Even-Numbered Rolls.

Name: Bolt Strike
Description: Bolt Strike Paralyzes the target on 17+.

Name: Eerie Impulse
Description: The target’s Special Attack is lowered 2 Combat Stages.

Name: Charge
Description: If the user performs an Electric Move on their next turn that deals damage, add its Damage Dice Roll an extra time to the damage. Raise the user’s Special Defense 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Electric Terrain
Description: The field becomes Electrified for 5 rounds. While Electrified, Pokémon and Trainers touching the ground are immune to Sleep, and Electric-Type attacks used by Pokémon and Trainers touching the ground gain a +10 Bonus to Damage Rolls.

Name: Charge Beam
Description: If Charge Beam successfully hits a target, roll 1d20. On a roll of 7+, the user’s Special Attack is raised by +1 Combat Stage.

Name: Electrify
Description: Until the end of the user’s next turn, the target’s damaging Water-Type attacks and Melee attacks of any Type deal Electric-Type Damage instead of their usual Type.

Name: Discharge
Description: Discharge Paralyzes all legal targets on 15+.

Name: Electro Ball
Description: The user adds their Speed Stat, including Combat Stages, in addition to their Special Attack when determining the damage dealt by Electro Ball. The Defender in turn subtracts both their Special Defense and Speed Stats from the damage dealt before applying Type Effectiveness.

Name: Ion Deluge
Description: An ion cloud is dispersed in the targeted area. All Normal-Type Moves targeting into or originating from the area become Electric-Typed Moves.

Name: Magnet Rise
Description: The user gains the Levitate Ability for 5 turns. Magnet Rise may be activated as a Swift Action if the user is otherwise given an action that consumes a Command.

Name: Electroweb
Description: All Legal Targets are lowered 1 Speed Combat Stage.

Name: Magnetic Flux
Description: All targets with the Minus or Plus Ability have their Defense and Special Defense raised by +1 Combat Stage.

Name: Fusion Bolt
Description: If Fusion Flare was used this round or last round by any participant of the encounter, Fusion Bolt has its Damage Base increased by +3.

Name: Nuzzle
Description: Nuzzle Paralyzes the target.

Name: Parabolic Charge
Description: After the targets take damage, the user gains Hit Points equal to half of the total damage they dealt to all targets.

Name: Thunder Fang
Description: Thunder Fang Paralyzes or Flinches on 18-19 during Accuracy Check; flip a coin to determine whether the foe gets Paralyzed or Flinches. On 20 during Accuracy Check, the foe is Paralyzed and Flinched.

Name: Shock Wave
Description: Shock Wave cannot miss.

Name: Thunderbolt
Description: Thunderbolt Paralyzes the target on 19+.

Name: Spark
Description: Spark Paralyzes the target on 15+.

Name: Thunder Punch
Description: Thunder Punch Paralyzes the target on 19+.

Name: Thunder
Description: Thunder Paralyzes its target on 15+. If the target is in Sunny Weather, Thunder’s Accuracy Check is 11. If the target is in Rainy Weather, Thunder cannot miss. If the target is airborne as a result of Fly or Sky Drop, Thunder cannot miss.

Name: Thunder Shock
Description: Thunder Shock Paralyzes the target on 17+.

Name: Thunder Wave
Description: Thunder Wave cannot miss. Thunder Wave Paralyzes the target. Targets immune to Electric Attacks are immune to Thunder Wave’s effects.

Name: Volt Switch
Description: If Volt Switch successfully hits its target, the user deals damage and then immediately is returned to its Poké Ball in the same turn. A New Pokémon may immediately be sent out. Using Volt Switch lets a Trapped user be recalled.

Name: Volt Tackle
Description: Volt Tackle Paralyzes the target on 19+.

Name: Wild Charge
Description: None

Name: Zap Cannon
Description: Zap Cannon Paralyzes the target. Zap Cannon ignores the target’s Evasion if there are no other combatants or Rough or Blocking Terrain within 2 meters of the target.

Name: Aromatic Mist
Description: All allies in Aromatic Mist’s area of effect have their Special Defense raised 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Baby-Doll Eyes
Description: The target’s Attack is lowered 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Disarming Pulse
Description: Disarming Voice cannot miss.

Name: Charm
Description: Charm lowers the target’s Attack 2 Combat Stages.

Name: Draining Kiss
Description: After the target takes damage, the user gains Hit Points equal to half of the damage they dealt to the target.

Name: Crafty Shield
Description: If the user or an Ally within 2 meters of Crafty Shield’s user is hit by a Status Move, you may use Crafty Shield as an Interrupt. All targets in Crafty Shield’s areaof- effect including the user, are instead not hit by the triggering Move and do not suffer any of its effects.

Name: Fairy Lock
Description: All legal targets become Trapped and Slowed while the user remains in the encounter. This effect ends if the user switches or is Fainted.

Name: Misty Terrain
Description: The area becomes Misty for 5 turns. While Misty, all Pokémon and Trainers standing on the ground ignore the first turn of all Status Afflictions, and Dragon-type attacks targeting or originating from a grounded Pokémon or Trainer take a -10 Penalty to Damage Rolls.

Name: Flower Shield
Description: All Grass Type Pokémon in Flower Shield’s area of effect have their Defense raised by +2 Combat Stages.

Name: Moonblast
Description: Moonblast lowers the target’s Special Attack by 1 Combat Stage on 15+.

Name: Geomancy
Description: Set-Up Effect: The user may not shift this round. The user may create as many squares of Rough Terrain as it wants within a Burst 3 as plants burst through the ground, regardless of the surface material.Resolution Effect: The user raises its Special Attack, Special Defense, and Speed by 2 Combat Stages each.

Name: Moonlight
Description: Effect: The user regains Hit Points equal to half of its full Hit Point value. If it is Sunny, the user gains 2/3 of its full Hit Point value. If it is Rainy, Sand Storming or Hailing the user gains 1/4 of their full Hit Point value.

Name: Play Rough
Description: Play Rough lowers the target’s Attack 1 Combat Stage on 17-20 during Accuracy Check.

Name: Sweet Kiss
Description: The target becomes Confused. On miss, the target suffers a -2 penalty to Accuracy Rolls for one full round.

Name: Arm Thrust
Description: None

Name: Circle Throw
Description: The target is Pushed 6 meters minus their Weight Class. On 15+, the target is also Tripped.

Name: Aura Sphere
Description: Aura Sphere cannot miss.

Name: Close Combat
Description: The user’s Defense and Special Defense are each lowered by -1 Combat Stage.

Name: Brick Break
Description: Light Screen and Reflect may not be activated in response to Brick Break.

Name: Counter
Description: Counter may be used as a Reaction when the user is hit by a damaging Physical Attack. Resolve the Triggering Attack, with Counter’s user resisting the attack one step further. After the attack is resolved, if Counter’s user was not Fainted, the triggering foe then loses Hit Points equal to twice the amount of Hit Points lost by the user from the triggering attack. Note that Counter is Physical, and while it cannot miss, it cannot hit targets immune to Fighting-Type Moves.

Name: Bulk Up
Description: Raise the user’s Attack 1 Combat Stage and raise the user’s Defense 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Cross Chop
Description: Cross Chop is a Critical Hit on 16+.

Name: Dynamic Punch
Description: Dynamic Punch Confuses the target. Dynamic Punch ignores the target’s Evasion if they are Flanked.

Name: Detect
Description: If the user is hit by a Move, the user may use Detect. The user is instead not hit by the Move. You do not take any damage nor are you affected by any of the Move’s effects.

Name: Final Gambit
Description: Final Gambit lowers the user to 0 Hit Points and causes them to Faint. Final Gambit then deals 1 point of damage to the target for every Hit Point lost by the user. Final Gambit does not cause items to activate.

Name: Double Kick
Description: None

Name: Flying Press
Description:
Flying Press may deal Flying Type damage if the user wishes.

Note: If Flying Press is Move Sync’d, it only changes the Fighting Type portion of the Move. You can still only choose between that Type and Flying Type; you cannot shift Flying Press to change the Flying part to another Type.

Name: Drain Punch
Description: After the target takes damage, the user gains HP equal to half of the damage they dealt to the target.

Name: Focus Blast
Description: Focus Blast lowers the target’s Special Defense 1 Combat Stage on 18+.

Name: High Jump Kick
Description: If High Jump Kick misses, the user loses Hit Points equal to 1/4th of their Max Hit Points. A failure to hit due to a Move with the Shield keyword does not count as a miss. This Move cannot be used if Gravity is in effect.

Name: Focus Punch
Description: Use of Focus Punch must be declared as a Priority (Limited) action at the beginning of the round. Nothing happens at this time. At the end of the round, if the target hasn’t been hit by an attack dealing damage equal to at least 25% of the user’s Maximum Hit Points, the user may Shift and use Focus Punch. Focus Punch’s Frequency is not expended if it is negated by an attack.

Name: Jump Kick
Description: If Jump Kick misses, the user loses Hit Points equal to 1/4th of their Max Hit Points. A failure to hit due to a Move with the Shield keyword does not count as a miss. This Move cannot be used if Gravity is in effect.

Name: Force Palm
Description: Force Palm Paralyzes the target on 18+.

Name: Karate Chop
Description: Karate Chop is a Critical Hit on 17+.

Name: Hammer Arm
Description: The user lowers their Speed 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Low Kick
Description: Low Kick’s Damage Base is equal to twice the target’s Weight Class.

Name: Power-Up Punch
Description: If Power-Up Punch successfully hits a target, the user’s Attack is raised by +1 Combat Stage

Name: Low Sweep
Description: Lowers the target’s Speed 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Quick Guard
Description: If the user or an adjacent ally is targeted by a Priority or Interrupt Attack, Quick Guard may be declared as an Interrupt, causing the triggering attack to have no effect.

Name: Mach Punch
Description: None

Name: Revenge
Description: When declaring Revenge, the user does nothing and may not Shift. At the end of the round, the user may shift and use Revenge. If the target has damaged the user this round, Revenge has a Damage Base of 12 (3d12+10 / 30).

Name: Mat Block
Description: If the user or an adjacent ally is hit by a damaging attack, the user may use Mat Block. The attack instead does not hit any targets, and it deals no damage and no has effects. You may only use Mat Block during the first round of an encounter.

Name: Reversal
Description: For each Injury the user has, Reversal’s Damage Base is increased by +1.

Name: Rock Smash
Description: Rock Smash lowers the target’s Defense 1 Combat Stage on 17+.

Name: Seismic Toss
Description: The target loses Hit Points equal to the level of Seismic Toss’ user.

Name: Rolling Kick
Description: Rolling Kick Flinches the target on 15+.

Name: Sky Uppercut
Description: Sky Uppercut may be used as an Interrupt when against a target initiating Bounce, Fly, or Sky Drop to allow the user to Shift and use Sky Uppercut. If Sky Uppercut successfully hits its target, the triggering Move fails (though the target may take their next turn normally).

Name: Sacred Sword
Description: Sacred Sword cannot miss.

Name: Storm Throw
Description: If Storm Throw hits, it is a Critical Hit.

Name: Secret Sword
Description: When calculating damage, the target subtracts their Defense from Secret Sword’s damage instead of their Special Defense. Secret Sword is still otherwise Special ( Special Evasion is used to avoid it, Mirror Coat can reflect it, etc. ).

Name: Submission
Description: On an accuracy roll of 15+, the target is Tripped.

Name: Superpower
Description: Superpower lowers the user’s Attack and Defense by 1 Combat Stage each.

Name: Vital Throw
Description: If the user is targeted by a Melee attack and has not yet taken a turn this round, the user may declare Vital Throw. After the triggering attack is resolved, the user may use Vital Throw against the triggering foe as a Reaction. Vital Throw cannot miss.

Name: Triple Kick
Description: Make three attacks with Triple Kick. If you hit once, Triple Kick has a DB of 1. If you hit two times, Triple Kick has a DB of 3. If you hit three times, Triple Kick has a DB of 6.

Name: Wake-Up Slap
Description: If the target is Asleep, Wake-Up Slap has a Damage Base of 10 (3d8+10 / 24) instead, and cures the target of Sleep.

Name: Vacuum Wave
Description: None

Name: Eruption
Description: For each 10% of Hit Points the user is missing, Eruption’s Damage Base is reduced by 1. Eruption creates a 1 meter burst, but also affects an area 10 meters tall straight up.

Name: Blaze Kick
Description: Blaze Kick Burns the target on 19+, and is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Name: Fiery Dance
Description: If Fiery Dance successfully hits a foe, it raises the user’s Special Attack by 1 Combat Stage on Even-Numbered Rolls.

Name: Blue Flare
Description: Blue Flare Burns the target on 17+.

Name: Fire Blast
Description: Fire Blast burns the target on 19+.

Name: Ember
Description: Ember Burns the target on 18+.

Name: Fire Fang
Description: Fire Fang Burns or Flinches on 18-19 during Accuracy Check; flip a coin to determine whether the foe gets Burned or Flinches. On 20 during Accuracy Check, the foe is Burned and Flinches.

Name: Fire Spin
Description: The target is put in a Vortex.

Name: Fire Pledge
Description: If an ally uses Grass Pledge or Water Pledge, you may use Fire Pledge as Priority (Advanced) immediately after their turn to target the same foe. If used in conjunction with Grass Pledge, Fire Hazards are created in a Burst 1 around the target. If used in conjunction with Water Pledge, a Rainbow is created that lasts for 5 rounds. Consult the Pledge keyword for additional details.

Name: Flame Burst
Description: Any Trainers or Pokémon cardinally adjacent to the target lose 5 Hit Points.

Name: Flame Charge
Description: Raise the user’s Speed 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Fire Punch
Description: Fire Punch Burns the target on 19+ during Accuracy Check.

Name: Flame Wheel
Description: Flame Wheel Burns the target on 19+.

Name: Flamethrower
Description: Flamethrower Burns the target on 19+.

Name: Heat Wave
Description: Heat Wave Burns all Legal Targets on 18+.

Name: Flare Blitz
Description: Flare Blitz Burns the target on 19+.

Name: Incinerate
Description: If a target is holding a Held Item or Main or Off- Hand item, they must either drop it immediately or lose a Tick of Hit Points. This may only cause a target to lose at most one Tick of Hit Points, no matter how many items they were holding.

Name: Fusion Flare
Description: If Fusion Bolt was used this round or last round by any participant of the encounter, Fusion Flare has its Damage Base increased by +3.

Name: Inferno
Description: Inferno Burns the target. Inferno ignores the target’s Evasion if there are no other combatants or Rough or Blocking Terrain within 2 meters of the target.

Name: Heat Crash
Description: For each weight class the user is above the target, increase Heat Crash’s Damage Base by +2.

Name: Lava Plume
Description: Lava Plume burns all targets on 16+.

Name: Magma Storm
Description: The target is put in a Vortex; this effect occurs even if Magma Storm misses its target.

Name: Searing Shot
Description: Searing Shot Burns all targets on 15+.

Name: Mystical Fire
Description: Mystical Fire lowers the target’s Special Attack by 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Sunny Day
Description: The weather becomes Sunny for 5 rounds. While Sunny, Fire-Type Attacks gain a +5 bonus to Damage Rolls, and Water-Type Attacks suffer a -5 Damage penalty.

Name: Overheat
Description: Lower the user’s Special Attack 2 Combat Stages after damage.

Name: V-Create
Description: Lower the user’s Defense, Special Defense, and Speed by 1 CS each.

Name: Sacred Fire
Description: Sacred Fire Burns the target on Even-Numbered Rolls.

Name: Will-O-Wisp
Description: The target is Burned.

Name: Acrobatics
Description: If the user is not holding an item, Acrobatics instead has a Damage Base of 11 (3d10+10 / 27).

Name: Air Slash
Description: Air Slash Flinches the target on 15+.

Name: Aerial Ace
Description: Aerial Ace cannot miss.

Name: Bounce
Description: The user first Shifts, gaining a +1 Bonus to Movement Speed and to their Jump Capabilities. After the user Shifts, they may attack with Bounce. The target becomes Vulnerable, and is Paralyzed on 16+.

Name: Aeroblast
Description: Aeroblast is a Critical Hit on an Even-Numbered Roll.

Name: Brave Bird
Description: The target is pushed back 2 meters.

Name: Air Cutter
Description: Air Cutter is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Name: Chatter
Description: Chatter confuses all targets on 16+.

Name: Defog
Description: The Weather becomes Clear, and all Blessings, Coats, and Hazards are destroyed. Clear Weather is the default weather, conferring no innate bonuses or penalties of any sort.

Name: Fly
Description:
Set-Up Effect: The user is moved up 25 meters into the air.

Resolution Effect: The user may shift twice while in the air, using their overland or sky speed, and then comes down next to a legal target, and attacks with Fly.

Name: Dragon Ascent
Description: The user’s Defense and Special Defense are each lowered by -1 Combat Stage.

Name: Gust
Description: If the target is airborne as a result of Fly or Sky Drop, Gust can hit them, ignoring Range and has a Damage Base of 8 instead.

Name: Drill Peck
Description: None

Name: Hurricane
Description: Hurricane Confuses its target on 15+. If the target is in Sunny Weather, Hurricane’s Accuracy Check is 11. If the target is in Rainy Weather, Hurricane cannot miss. If the target is airborne as a result of Fly or Sky Drop, Hurricane cannot miss.

Name: Feather Dance
Description: All legal targets have their Attack lowered 2 Combat Stages.

Name: Mirror Move
Description: Use the Move the target has used on their last turn. You may choose new targets for the Move. Mirror Move cannot miss.

Name: Roost
Description: The user regains Hit Points equal to half of its full Hit Points. If the user is a Flying Type, it loses the Flying Type until the start of their next turn.

Name: Oblivion Wing
Description: The user gains Hit Points equal to Oblivion Wing’s Damage Roll.

Name: Sky Attack
Description:
Set-Up Effect: The user is moved up 25 meters into the air.

Resolution Effect: The user may shift until they are next to a legal target in the encounter. They may then shift again, and pass through legal targets to attack with Sky Attack. Sky Attack Flinches a target on 17-20 during Accuracy Check.

Name: Peck
Description: None

Name: Sky Drop
Description:
Set-Up Effect: Make Sky Drop’s Accuracy Check. If the user hits, the user and target are moved 25 meters into the air. The target forfeits their next turn, and cannot Shift or take actions until Sky Drop is resolved.

Resolution Effect: Shift while in the air, and lower both the user and the target heights back to the ground. Then apply Sky Drop’s damage. If the target has a Sky or Levitate Speed, Sky Drop fails to deal damage. If the user is Fainted after the Set-Up but before the Resolution, the target falls to the ground and takes damage as if Sky Drop had a Damage Base of 3 (1d6+5/8) unless they have a Sky or Levitate Speed, in which case they take no damage.

Name: Tailwind
Description: For the remainder of the encounter, all allied trainers and Pokémon gain +5 to their Initiative. Multiple instances of Tailwind cannot stack.

Name: Wing Attack
Description: None

Name: Astonish
Description: Astonish Flinches the target on 15+. Once per scene, if the target is unaware of the user’s presence, Astonish automatically Flinches the target.

Name: Destiny Bond
Description: All enemy targets in the burst become Bound to the user until the end of the user’s next turn. If a Bound target causes the user to Faint through a Damaging Attack, the Bound target immediately faints after their attack is resolved.

Name: Confuse Ray
Description: The target is Confused.

Name: Grudge
Description: You may use Grudge as an Interrupt when a Damaging Attack causes the user to faint. Grudge is activated as a Free Action (does not take up a Command). The attack is resolved as usual, and the user Faints. The attacker that caused the user to Faint becomes Suppressed for the remainder of the encounter; switching and Taking a Breather does not end Suppression when used this way.

Name: Curse
Description: If the user is not a Ghost Type, Curse has a Frequency of EOT, and when used the user lowers its Speed by -1 Combat Stage, but raises Attack and Defense by +1 Combat Stage each. If the user is a Ghost Type, Curse has a Frequency of Scene, and when used the user loses 1/3rd of their Max Hit Points and a target Pokémon or Trainer within 8 meters of the user becomes Cursed. This Hit Point loss cannot be prevented in any way.

Name: Hex
Description: Once a Scene, if Hex’s target has a Status Affliction, you may have Hex’s Damage Base be 13 instead (4d10+10 / 35).

Name: Lick
Description: Lick Paralyzes the target on 15+ during Accuracy Check.

Name: Phantom Force
Description:
Set-Up Effect: The user is removed from the field, and their turn ends.

Resolution Effect: Phantom Force’s user appears adjacent to any legal target on the field, ignoring Movement Capabilities, and then uses Phantom Force’s attack. Phantom Force cannot be avoided by Moves with the Shield Keyword, the Dodge Ability, or similar effects, and Intercepts may not be attempted in response.

Name: Night Shade
Description: The target loses Hit Points equal to the level of Night Shade’s user. Do not apply weakness or resistance. Do not apply stats.

Name: Shadow Ball
Description: Shadow Ball lowers the foe’s Special Defense 1 Combat Stage on 17+.

Name: Nightmare
Description: Nightmare can only hit Legal Targets that are Asleep. The target gains Bad Sleep.

Name: Shadow Claw
Description: Shadow Claw is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Name: Ominous Wind
Description: On 19+, the user has each of its stats raised by +1 Combat Stage.

Name: Shadow Force
Description:
Set-Up Effect: The user is removed from the field, and their turn ends.

Resolution Effect: Shadow Force’s user appears adjacent to any legal Target, ignoring Movement Capabilities, and then uses Shadow Force’s attack. Shadow Force cannot be avoided by Moves with the Shield Keyword, the Dodge Ability, or similar effects, and Intercepts may not be attempted in response.

Name: Spite
Description: Spite may be used as a Free Action that does not take up a Command whenever the user is hit by a Move. That Move becomes Disabled for the attacker.

Name: Trick-or-Treat
Description: The target gains the Ghost Type in addition to its other Types for 5 turns.

Name: Shadow Punch
Description: Shadow Punch cannot miss.

Name: Shadow Sneak
Description: None

Name: Absorb
Description: After the target takes damage, the user gains Hit Points equal to half of the damage they dealt to the target.

Name: Cotton Spore
Description: All Legal Targets have their Speed lowered 2 Combat Stages.

Name: Aromatherapy
Description: All allies in the burst are cured of one status condition of their choice.

Name: Energy Ball
Description: Energy Ball lowers the foe’s Special Defense 1 Combat Stage on 17+.

Name: Forest's Curse
Description: The target gains the Grass Type in addition to its other Types for 5 turns.

Name: Cotton Guard
Description: Raise the user’s Defense 3 Combat Stages.

Name: Giga Drain
Description: After the target takes damage, the user gains Hit Points equal to half of the damage they dealt to the target.

Name: Grass Whistle
Description: The target falls Asleep.

Name: Grass Knot
Description: Grass Knot’s Damage Base is equal to twice the target’s Weight Class.

Name: Grassy Terrain
Description: The area becomes Grassy for 5 rounds. While Grassy, all Pokémon and Trainers standing on the ground recover a Tick of Hit Points at the start of every turn, and Grass-Type attacks performed by grounded Pokémon and Trainers gain a +10 bonus to Damage Rolls.

Name: Grass Pledge
Description: If an ally uses Fire Pledge or Water Pledge, you may use Grass Pledge as Priority (Advanced) immediately after their turn to target the same foe. If used in conjunction with Fire Pledge, Fire Hazards are created in a Burst 1 around the target. If used in conjunction with Water Pledge, the target and all foes adjacent to the target are slowed and have their Speed reduced by 2 Combat Stages. Consult the Pledge keyword for additional details.

Name: Horn Leech
Description: After the target takes damage, the user gains Hit Points equal to half of the damage they dealt to thetarget.

Name: Ingrain
Description: Ingrain applies a Coat to the user, which has the following effect; the user cannot be pushed or pulled, and cannot be switched out. At the beginning of each of the user’s turn, the user gains a Tick of Hit Points.

Name: Leaf Blade
Description: Leaf Blade is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Name: Magical Leaf
Description: Magical Leaf cannot miss.

Name: Leaf Storm
Description: Lower the user’s Special Attack 2 Combat Stages after damage.

Name: Mega Drain
Description: After the target takes damage, the user gains Hit Points equal to half of the damage they dealt to the target.

Name: Leaf Tornado
Description: Small or Medium targets in the central square of the blast are not hit. On 15+, all legal targets have their Accuracy lowered by -1.

Name: Needle Arm
Description: Needle Arm Flinches the target on 15+.

Name: Leech Seed
Description: At the beginning of each of the target’s turns, Leech Seed’s target loses a Tick of Hit Points. Leech Seed’s user then gains Hit Points equal to the amount the target lost. Leech Seed lasts until the target faints or is returned to a Poké Ball. Grass Types and targets immune to Grass Attacks are immune to Leech Seed.

Name: Petal Dance
Description: After damage is dealt, the user becomes Enraged and Confused.

Name: Seed Flare
Description: All Legal Targets have their Special Defense lowered 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Sleep Powder
Description: The Target Falls Asleep

Name: Razor Leaf
Description: Razor Leaf is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Name: Solar Beam
Description: Set-Up Effect: If the weather is not Sunny, the user’s turn ends. If the weather is Sunny, immediately proceed to the Resolution Effect instead and this Move loses the Set-Up keyword. Resolution Effect: The user attacks with Solar Beam. If the weather is Rainy, Sandstorming, or Hailing, Solar Beam’s Damage Base is lowered to 6 (2d6+8 / 15).

Name: Spiky Shield
Description: If the user is hit by an attack, the user may useSpiky Shield. The user is instead not hit by the Move.You do not take any damage nor are you affected by anyof the Move’s effects. In addition, if the triggering attackwas Melee ranged, the attacker loses a Tick of Hit Points.

Name: Spore
Description: The target falls Asleep

Name: Stun Spore
Description: The target is Paralyzed

Name: Worry Seed
Description: You choose one of the target’s Abilities. Worry Seed changes that Ability to Insomnia for the remainder of the encounter.

Name: Synthesis
Description: The user regains Hit Points equal to half of its full Hit Point value. If it is Sunny, the user gains 2/3 of its full Hit Point value instead. If it is Rainy, Sand Storming or Hailing the user gains 1/4 of their full Hit Point value instead.

Name: Bone Club
Description: Bone Club Flinches the target on 18+.

Name: Dig
Description:
Set-Up Effect: The user shifts 25 meters underground and their turn ends.

Resolution Effect: The user may shift horizontally using their burrow or overland speed, and then shifts 25 meters straight up. Upon reaching the surface, the user attacks with Dig, creating a Burst 1.

Name: Bone Rush
Description: None

Name: Drill Run
Description: Drill Run is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Name: Bonemerang
Description: None

Name: Earth Power
Description: Earth Power lowers the Special Defense of all Legal Targets 1 Combat Stage on 16+.

Name: Bulldoze
Description: All Legal Targets are lowered 1 Speed Combat Stage.

Name: Earthquake
Description: Earthquake can hit targets that are underground, including those using the Move Dig.

Name: Mud Bomb
Description: The target’s Accuracy is lowered by -1 on 16+.

Name: Fissure
Description: Roll 1d100. This roll may not be modified in any way. If you roll X or lower, the target Faints. X is equal to 30 + The User’s Level - The Target’s Level.

Name: Mud Shot
Description: The target’s Speed is lowed by -1 Combat Stage.

Name: Mud Sport
Description: All targets in the burst, including the user, gain a Coat which grants them 1 Step of Resistance to Electric Type Moves. After a target has been hit by a damaging Electric Type Move, the coat is removed.

Name: Land's Wrath
Description: None

Name: Mud-Slap
Description: The target’s Accuracy is lowered by -1.

Name: Magnitude
Description: When you use Magnitude, roll 1d6. Magnitude’s Damage Base is equal to 5+X, where X is the value of the d6. Magnitude can hit targets that are underground, including those using the Move Dig.

Name: Precipice Blades
Description: None

Name: Spikes
Description: Set 8 square meters of Spikes within your range, all 8 meters must be adjacent with at least one other space of Spikes. Spikes cause terrain to count as Slow Terrain, and a grounded foe that runs into the hazards will lose a Tick of Hit Points and become Slowed until the end of their next turn.

Name: Rototiller
Description: All Grass-type Pokémon in the area raise their Attack and Special Attack 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Sand Tomb
Description: The target is put in a Vortex.

Name: Sand Attack
Description: The target is Blinded until the end of their next turn.

Name: Aurora Beam
Description: Aurora Beam lowers the target’s Attack 1 Combat Stage on 18+.

Name: Freeze-Dry
Description: When calculating Weakness and Resistance for Freeze-Dry, Water-Typed targets calculate damage as if Water was weak to Ice.

Name: Avalanche
Description: When declaring Avalanche, the user does nothing and may not Shift. At the end of the round, the user Shifts and uses Avalanche on any legal target. If the target damaged the user this round, Avalanche has a Damage Base of 12 (4d10+15 / 40) instead.

Name: Freeze Shock
Description: Set-Up Effect: The user may shift, then ends their turn. Resolution Effect: The user uses Freeze Shock. Freeze Shock paralyzes on 15+.

Name: Frost Breath
Description: If Frost Breath hits, it is a Critical Hit.

Name: Blizzard
Description: Blizzard Freezes all legal target on 15+. If the target is in Hailing Weather, Blizzard cannot miss.

Name: Glaciate
Description: All Legal Targets have their Speed lowered 1 Combat Stage. On an Even-Numbered Roll, all Legal Targets on the ground are Slowed.

Name: Ice Beam
Description: Ice Beam Freezes on 19+ during Accuracy Check.

Name: Ice Burn
Description:
Set-Up Effect: The user may shift, then ends their turn. 

Resolution Effect: The user uses Ice Burn. Ice Burn Burns on 15+.

Name: Hail
Description: The weather changes to Hail for 5 rounds. While it is Hailing, all non-Ice Type Pokémon lose a Tick of Hit Points at the beginning of their turn.

Name: Haze
Description: The Combat Stages of the user and all Pokémon and Trainers in the encounter are set to their default state (usually 0).

Name: Ice Fang
Description: Ice Fang Freezes or Flinches on 18+ during Accuracy Check; flip a coin to determine whether the foe gets Frozen or Flinches. On 20 during Accuracy Check, the foe is Frozen and Flinches.

Name: Ice Ball
Description: The user continues to use Ice Ball on each of its turns until they miss any target with Ice Ball, or are not able to hit any target with Ice Ball during their turn. Each successive use of Ice Ball increases Ice Ball’s Damage Base by +3 to a maximum of DB 15.

Name: Ice Punch
Description: Ice Punch Freezes the target on 19+ during Accuracy Check.

Name: Ice Shard
Description: None

Name: Mist
Description: Blessing – Any user affected by Mist may activate it when having Combat Stages lowered by any effect; if they do, those Combat Stages are instead not lowered. Mist may be activated 3 times, and then disappears.

Name: Icicle Crash
Description: Icicle Crash Flinches the target on 15+.

Name: Powder Snow
Description: Powder Snow Freezes all Legal Targets on 19+.

Name: Icicle Spear
Description: None

Name: Sheer Cold
Description: Roll 1d100. This roll may not be modified in any way. If you roll X or lower, the target Faints. X is equal to 30 + The User’s Level - The Target’s Level.

Name: Icy Wind
Description: All Legal Targets have their Speed lowered 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Acupressure
Description: Roll 1d6. On a result of 1, raise the target’s Attack 2 Combat Stages. On a result of 2, raise the target’s Defense 2 Combat Stages. On a result of 3, raise the target’s Special Attack 2 Combat Stages. On a result of 4, raise the target’s Special Defense 2 Combat Stages. On a result of 5, raise the target’s Speed 2 Combat Stages. On a result of 6, raise the target’s Accuracy by +2.

Name: Attract
Description: Attract Infatuates the target if its gender is the opposite of the user’s. Attract fails when used by or against Genderless targets.

Name: Barrage
Description: None

Name: After You
Description: After You is a Swift Action. The target takes their turn for the round immediately after the user finishes their turn, ignoring Initiative. After You may only affect a target that has not yet acted that round and can only affect willing targets.

Name: Batton Pass
Description: The user is replaced with another Pokémon from their trainer’s roster. All Combat Stage, Coats, and [Stratagems] on Baton Pass’ user are transferred to the replacement. Baton Pass may be used to switch even if the user is Trapped.

Name: Assist
Description: Randomly select another Pokémon on the user’s roster and then randomly select a Move that Pokémon knows. Assist’s user uses that Move immediately.

Name: Belly Drum
Description: The user gains +6 Attack Combat Stages, and loses Hit Points equal to ½ of their Max Hit Points.

Name: Bestow
Description: The user gives its held item to the target, unless the target is already holding an item. Using Bestow is a Swift Action.

Name: Body Slam
Description: Body Slam Paralyzes the target on 15+.

Name: Bide
Description: The user may use Bide as a Reaction Move upon being Hit by a Damaging Move. During their next available turn, the user may Shift and then use Bide, causing all Adjacent foes to lose X HP, where X is the amount of Damage taken since declaring use of Bide (Loss of life through effects such as Poison is not ‘Damage’).

Name: Boomburst
Description: None

Name: Camouflage
Description: The user changes their Type to match the field. Forests and grassy areas change the user into GrassType. Watery areas change the user into Water-Type. Caves and Mountains could change the user into RockType or Ground-Type. An icy terrain would turn the user into Ice-Type. A building may change the user into Steel-Type or Normal-Type. Weather affects what Type the user becomes. Use common sense, if you are having difficult determining what type the user should become, consult the GM.

Name: Bind
Description: The user gains a +1 Bonus to Accuracy Rolls made to initiate Grapple Maneuvers, and +2 to Skill Checks made to initiate Grapple Maneuvers or gain Dominance. Whenever the user gains Dominance in a Grapple, the target of the Grapple loses a Tick of Hit Points.

Name: Block
Description: The target is Stuck and Trapped until the beginning of your next turn.

Name: Captivate
Description: Captivate lowers the target’s Special Attack 2 Combat Stages. Captivate may not affect something that is the same gender as the user or something that is genderless.

Name: Constrict
Description: Constrict lowers the target’s Speed 1 Combat Stage. Constrict may be used as a Swift Action against targets the user is Grappling, and automatically hits when performed this way

Name: Chip Away
Description: Ignore any Armor, Damage Reduction, or changes in the target’s Defense or Special Defense (such as from Combat Stages) when calculating damage.

Name: Conversion
Description: The user becomes the elemental Type of their choice as long as they have a Move that is the same elemental Type until the end of the encounter. Replace all other Types.

Name: Comet Punch
Description: None

Name: Conversion2
Description: The user becomes the elemental Type of their choice as long as the Type resists the elemental Type of the Move it last took damage from until the end of the encounter. Replace all other Types.

Name: Confide
Description: The target’s Special Attack is lowered 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Copycat
Description: Use the Move the target has used on their last turn. You may choose new targets for the Move. Copycat cannot miss.

Name: Covet
Description: Covet takes the target’s Held Item or Accessory Slot Item and attaches it to Covet’s user, if the user is not holding anything

Name: Defence Curl
Description: The user becomes Curled Up. While Curled Up, the user becomes immune to Critical Hits and gains 10 Damage Reduction. However, while Curled Up, the user is Slowed and their Accuracy is lowered by -4. The user may stop being Curled Up as a Swift Action. If the user has Rollout or Ice Ball in their Move List, they do not become Slowed while Curled Up. Furthermore, when using the Moves Rollout or Ice Ball while Curled Up, the user gains a +10 bonus to the damage rolls of those Moves and does not suffer Accuracy Penalties from being Curled Up.

Name: Crush Claw
Description: Crush Claw lowers the target’s Defense 1 Combat Stage on Even-Numbered Rolls.

Name: Disable
Description: Disable may be used as a Free Action that does not take up a Command whenever the user is hit by a Move. That Move becomes Disabled for the attacker.

Name: Crush Grip
Description: For every 10% the target is below their full Hit Points, Crush Grip’s Damage Base is reduced by 1.

Name: Dizzy Punch
Description: Dizzy Punch Confuses the target on 17+

Name: Cut
Description: Cut ignores up to 5 Damage Reduction (Defenses are not Damage Reduction).

Name: Double Hit
Description: None

Name: Echoed Voice
Description: If Echoed Voice was used by any Pokémon or Trainer in the Encounter on the previous round, increase its Damage Base by +4. If Echoed Voice was used by any Pokémon or Trainers during both the previous two rounds, increase its Damage Base by +8.

Name: Double Team
Description: The user gains 3 activations of Double Team. The user may either activate Double Team when being targeted by an attack to increase their Evasion by +2 against that attack; or when making an attack to increase their Accuracy by +2 for that attack.

Name: Egg Bomb
Description: None

Name: Double-Edge
Description: None

Name: Encore
Description: Roll 1d6. On a result of 1 or 2, the target becomes Confused; on a result of 3 or 4 the target becomes Suppressed; on a result of 5 or 6 the target becomes Enraged.

Name: Double Slap
Description: None

Name: Endeavor
Description: The target loses a Tick of Hit Points for each Injury the user has.

Name: Endure
Description: If the user is hit by a damaging Move, you may use Endure as a Free Action. If the Move would bring Endure’s user down to 0 Hit Points or less, Endure’s user instead is set to 1 Hit Point.

Name: Facade
Description: If the user is afflicted with a Persistent Status Affliction, Façade’s Damage Base is doubled to DB 14 (4d10+15 / 40).

Name: Entrainment
Description: The target gains one of the user’s Abilities for 3 turns.

Name: Fake Out
Description: You may only use Fake Out with Priority upon joining an encounter; if you do, Fake Out Flinches the target. Switching out resets the requirement of joining an encounter

Name: Explosion
Description: The user’s Hit Points are set to -50% of their full Hit Point value. This Hit Point loss cannot be prevented or reduced in any way. The user’s loyalty toward its trainer may be lowered.

Name: False Swipe
Description: False Swipe’s damage cannot bring a target lower than 1 Hit Point.

Name: Extreme Speed
Description: None

Name: Feint
Description: If a foe uses a Move with the Shield Keyword in response to one of your actions, you may activate Feint to cause the triggering Move to Fail. Feint is activated as a Free Action.

Name: Flail
Description: For each Injury the user has, Flail’s Damage Base is increased by +1.

Name: Foresight
Description: Foresight may be activated as a Swift Action on the user’s turn. For the rest of the turn, the user’s Normal-Type and Fighting-Type Moves can hit and affect Ghost-Type targets, and the user can see through the Illusion Ability, Moves with the Illusion keyword, and effects created by the Illusionist Capability, ignoring all effects from those.

Name: Flash
Description: The Accuracy of all Legal Targets is lowered by -1.

Name: Frustration
Description: Frustration’s Damage Base is equal to 9 minus the user’s Loyalty Value. Using Frustration may make your Pokémon dislike you.

Name: Focus Energy
Description: The user becomes Pumped. While Pumped, the user’s Critical Range is extended by 2, or 18+ if the Critical Range is not otherwise extended. Being switched will cause this effect to end.

Name: Fury Attack
Description: None

Name: Follow Me
Description: Until the end of the user’s next turn, all Foes must target the user when using a Move that targets their opponents. This effect ends if the user is Fainted or Switched out.

Name: Fury Swipes
Description: None

Name: Giga Impact
Description: None

Name: Guillotine
Description: Roll 1d100. This roll may not be modified in any way. If you roll X or lower, the target Faints. X is equal to 30 + The User’s Level - The Target’s Level.

Name: Glare
Description: Glare Paralyzes the target.

Name: Harden
Description: Raise the user’s Defense 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Growl
Description: Growl lowers all Legal Targets Attack 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Headbutt
Description: Headbutt Flinches the target on 15+.

Name: Growth
Description: Raise the user’s Attack 1 Combat Stage and raise the user’s Special Attack 1 Combat Stage. If it is Sunny, double the amount of Combat Stages gained.

Name: Head Charge
Description: The target is Pushed back 2 meters.

Name: Heal Bell
Description: All targets are cured of any Persistent Status ailments.

Name: Hold Hands
Description: Both the user and the target become Cheered. They may give up the Cheered condition when making a Save Check to roll twice and take the best result.

Name: Helping Hand
Description: Helping Hand grants the target +2 on their next Accuracy Roll this round, and +10 to the next Damage Roll this round.

Name: Horn Attack
Description: None

Name: Hidden Power
Description: When a Pokémon first obtains the Move Hidden Power, roll 1d20. Hidden Power’s Elemental Type will be changed from Normal to Bug on a result of 1; Dark on 2; Dragon on 3; Electric on 4; Fairy on 5; Fighting on 6; Fire on 7; Flying on 8; Ghost on 9; Grass on 10; Ground on 11; Ice on 12; Normal on 13; Poison on 14; Psychic on 15; Rock on 16; Steel on 17; Water on 18; and on 19 or 20, reroll until you roll another number. This effect is permanent –if Hidden Power is forgotten and relearned, the chosen Type remains the same

Name: Howl
Description: Raise the user’s Attack 1 Combat stage.

Name: Hyper Beam
Description: None

Name: Last Resort
Description: Last Resort can only be used after the user has performed 5 other different Moves in its Move List during a single fight, without being switched out.

Name: Hyper Fang
Description: Hyper Fang Flinches the target on 19+

Name: Leer
Description: All legal targets have their Defense lowered by 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Hyper Voice
Description: All Legal Targets are pushed back to the squares immediately outside the blast, away from the user.

Name: Lock-On
Description: The target is Locked-On. The next Move that the user uses against the Target that requires an Accuracy Check cannot miss. Lock-On’s effect, on both the User and Target, is passed on by Baton Pass.

Name: Judgment
Description: Judgment’s Type can be whatever Elemental Type the user wants it to be.

Name: Lovely Kiss
Description: The target falls Asleep.

Name: Lucky Chant
Description: Blessing – Any user affected by Lucky Chant may activate it when receiving a Critical Hit to cause the attack to instead deal damage as if it was not a Critical Hit. Lucky Chant may be activated 3 times, and then disappears.

Name: Mega Punch
Description: None

Name: Me First
Description: If an opponent declares a Damaging Attack against the user, and Me First’s user has a higher Speed stat then the target, the user may use Me First as an Interrupt. The User will then use the same Move the triggering foe was about to use on that foe

Name: Metronome
Description: Metronome randomly uses any other Move except for After You, Assist, Bestow, Copycat, Counter, Covet, Crafty Shield, Destiny Bond, Detect, Endure, Feint, Focus Punch, Follow Me, Helping Hand, King’s Shield, Metronome, Me First, Mimic, Mirror Coat, Mirror Move, Protect, Quash, Quick Guard, Rage Powder, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Snatch, Snore, Spiky Shield, Switcheroo, Thief, Transform, Trick, and Wide Guard. The GM helps to pick the random Move.

Name: Mean Look
Description: The user casts a foul spell on the target, causing it to become Trapped and Slowed for the remainder of he encounter.

Name: Milk Drink
Description: The target regains Hit Points equal to half of its full Hit Point value. The user may target themselves with Milk Drink.

Name: Mega Kick
Description: The target is Pushed 2 meters.

Name: Mimic
Description: Choose a Move that the target has used during the encounter. For the remainder of the encounter, that Move replaces Mimic on the user’s Move List. Mimic cannot miss.

Name: Morning Sun
Description: The user regains Hit Points equal to half of its full Hit Point value. If it is Sunny, the user gains 2/3 of its full Hit Point value. If it is Rainy, Sand Storming or Hailing the user gains 1/4 of their full Hit Point value.

Name: Mind Reader
Description: The target becomes Read to the user until the end of the user’s next turn. The user may end this effect when making an Attack on the user, causing that attack to automatically hit; OR when the Read target uses an Attack against the user, causing that attack to automatically miss. If the user has the Telepathy Capability, the user automatically succeeds on a mindreading attempt against the target, and may listen to the target’s surface thoughts as long as they remain Read. Mind Reader automatically misses against targets with the Mindlock Capability.

Name: Natural Gift
Description: Refer to the Move Keywords Berry list. Natural Gift deals damage according to the Berry list and Natural Gift’s Type is also defined there. The Berry’s Digestion Buff is nullified and is not used.

Name: Nature Power
Description: Nature Power uses a Move defined by the Environ keyword.

Name: Minimize
Description: The user gains +4 Evasion, and user’s size is lowered to Small for the remainder of the encounter.

Name: Noble Roar
Description: Noble Roar lowers all targets’ Attack and Special Attack by 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Odor Sleuth
Description: Odor Sleuth may be activated as a Swift Action on the user’s turn. For the rest of the turn, the user’s Normal-Type and Fighting-Type Moves can hit and affect Ghost-Type targets, and the user can see through the Illusion Ability, Moves with the Illusion keyword, and effects created by the Illusionist Capability, ignoring all effects from those.

Name: Perish Song
Description: Perish Song cannot miss. All targets, including the user, receive a Perish Count of 3. At the beginning of each of the target’s turns, their Perish count is lowered by 1. Once a Perish Count reaches 0, set the Pokémon’s Hit Points to 0. A Perish Count disappears if a target returns to their Poké Ball, Takes a Breather, or is knocked out. Perish Song never causes Massive Damage.

Name: Play Nice
Description: Play Nice lowers the target’s Attack by 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Pain Split
Description: The user and the target both lose ½ of their current Hit Points. Add the amount of Hit Points the user and the target lost together, and divide the value by 2. Both the target and the user gain Hit Points equal to this value. Do not add Injuries from Pain Split from Hit Point Markers until the full effect of the Move has been resolved. Pain Split never causes Massive Damage. Hit Point loss from Pain Split cannot be prevented in any way

Name: Pound
Description: None

Name: Pay Day
Description: Pay Day scatters metal coins equal in value to 1d8 times the user’s level. If it is a trainer battle, the winner of the battle gets to pick up the coins

Name: Present
Description: Roll 1d6; Present has a Damage Base equal to twice the result. On a result of 1, instead of taking damage, the target gains 20 Hit Points.

Name: Rage
Description: The user becomes Enraged. Until the end of the user’s next turn, if the user is Enraged, the user gains +1 Attack Combat Stage whenever they are damaged by an Damaging Move or Attack.

Name: Protect
Description: If the user is hit by a Move, the user may use Protect. The user is instead not hit by the Move. You do not take any damage nor are you affected by any of the Move’s effects.

Name: Rapid Spin
Description: Rapid Spin destroys all Hazards within 5 meters, removes Leech Seeds, and removes the user’s Trapped or Stuck status.

Name: Psych Up
Description: The user’s Combat Stages are changed to match the target’s Combat Stages. Psych Up cannot miss.

Name: Razor Wind
Description:
Set-Up Effect: The user may not shift this round. The user whips up a whirlwind around themselves, granting +2 Evasion until the end of their next turn, and destroying any Smokescreen or Hazards on any squares they are standing on and in all squares adjacent to them.

Resolution Effect: The user attacks with Razor Wind. Razor Wind is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Name: Quick Attack
Description: None

Name: Disarming Voice
Description: Disarming Voice cannot miss.

Name: Pluck
Description: Pluck takes the target’s Held Item or Accessory Slot Item and attaches it to Pluck’s user, if the user is not holding anything.

Name: Horn Drill
Description: Roll 1d100. This roll may not be modified in any way. If you roll X or lower, the target Faints. X is equal to 30 + The User’s Level - The Target’s Level.

Name: Recover
Description: The user regains Hit Points equal to half of its full Hit Point value.

Name: Relic Song
Description: All Legal Targets fall Asleep on 16+. As long as Meloetta knows Relic Song, it may change between Aria Form and Step Form as a Swift Action when using Relic Song, or as a Standard Action otherwise. Both Aria and Step Form must be statted with the same HP Stat.

Name: Recycle
Description: The effect of a consumable item used earlier in the encounter is used again as if it had not been destroyed. The item is still gone.

Name: Retaliate
Description: Retaliate’s Damage Base is doubled to DB 14 (4d10+15 / 40) if an ally has been Fainted by a Damaging Move used by the Target in the last 2 rounds of Combat.

Name: Reflect Type
Description: Reflect Type changes one of the user’s Types into one Type of your choice that the target has for the rest

Name: Return
Description: Return’s Damage Base is equal to 3 plus the user’s Loyalty Value.

Name: Refresh
Description: The user is cured of all Poison, Burns, and Paralysis.

Name: Roar
Description: When declaring Roar, the user does nothing and may not Shift. At the end of the round, the user Shifts and uses Roar. Targets hit by Roar immediately Shift away from the target using their highest usable movement capability, and towards their Trainer if possible. If the target is an owned Pokémon and ends this shift within 6 meters of their Poké Ball, they are immediately recalled to their Poké Ball. If that Trainer sends out a replacement, they do not lose their Pokémon turn.

Name: Safeguard
Description: Blessing – Any user affected by Safeguard may activate it when receiving a Status Affliction to ignore the effects of that Status Affliction on their next turn. Safeguard may be activated 3 times, and then disappears.

Name: Scary Face
Description: The target’s Speed is lowered 2 Combat Stages.

Name: Rock Climb
Description: Rock Climb Confuses the target on 17+.

Name: Scratch
Description: None

Name: Round
Description: Round’s Damage Base is equal to 6, plus +2 more for each previous use of Round by any Trainer or Pokémon this round, up to a maximum of DB12.

Name: Screech
Description: All Legal Targets have their Defense lowered 2 Combat Stages.

Name: Secret Power
Description: Secret Power’s effect depends on Environ. Secret Power’s effect activates on 17+.

Name: Simple Beam
Description: You choose one of the target’s Abilities. Simple Beam changes that Ability to Simple for the remainder of the encounter.

Name: Self-Destruct
Description: The user’s Hit Points are set to -50% of their full Hit Point value. This Hit Point loss may not be prevented or reduced in any way. The user’s loyalty toward its trainer may be lowered.

Name: Sing
Description: All legal Targets fall Asleep. On a miss, Sing instead causes targets to become Slowed and suffer a -2 penalty to their Evasion until the end of the user’s next turn.

Name: Sketch
Description: Sketch cannot miss. Once Sketch has been used, remove Sketch from the user’s Move list. The last Move that the target used is added to the user’s Move list permanently. Sketch may not be Interrupted or Intercepted.

Name: Sharpen
Description: Raise the user’s Attack 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Shell Smash
Description: Raise the user’s Attack 2 Combat Stages, raise the user’s Special Attack 2 Combat Stages and raise the user’s Speed 2 Combat Stages. Lower the user’s Defense 1 Combat Stage and lower the user’s Special Defense 1

Name: Skull Bash
Description:
Set-Up Effect: The use gains +1 Defense CS.
Resolution Effect: The user may attack with Skull Bash. The target is pushed 3 meters.

Name: Slack Off
Description: The user regains Hit Points equal to half of its full Hit Points.

Name: Smelling Salts
Description: If the target is Paralyzed, Smelling Salt’s Damage Base is doubled to 14 (4d10+15 / 40), and cures the target of Paralysis.

Name: Slam
Description: Slam may be used as a Free Action at the end of a Sprint Maneuver taken as a Standard Action, as long as the user Shifted at least 3 meters in a straight line towards the target. When used this way, Slam gains the Smite keyword.

Name: Smokescreen
Description: Smokescreen creates a blast of Smoke that covers the target area; the Smoke persists until the end of the encounter, or until Defog or Whirlwind are used. All targets attacking from or into the Smoke receive a -3 penalty to Accuracy.

Name: Slash
Description: Slash is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Name: Snore
Description: Snore Flinches all legal targets on 15+. Snore may only be used by Sleeping users.

Name: Sleep Talk
Description: Select another of the user’s Moves at random; this turn, the user may Shift and use that Move despite being Asleep. Sleep Talk can be only be used by Sleeping targets.

Name: Soft-Boiled
Description: The target regains Hit Points equal to half of its full Hit Points. The user may target themselves with Soft-Boiled.

Name: Sonic Boom
Description: Sonic Boom causes the target to lose 15 Hit Points. Sonic Boom is Special and interacts with other moves and effects as such ( Special Evasion may be applied to avoid it, Mirror Coat can reflect it, etc. )

Name: Stockpile
Description: The user adds 1 to their Stockpiled count to a maximum of 3. For each number a Stockpiled count is above 0, raise the user’s Defense 1 Combat Stage and raise the user’s Special Defense 1 Combat Stage. If a Stockpiled count is set to 0, the Combat Stages gained from the Stockpiled count are removed.

Name: Spike Cannon
Description: None

Name: Stomp
Description: Stomp Flinches the target on 15+. If the target is at least one size category smaller than the user, Stomp deals an additional 10 damage.

Name: Spit Up
Description: For each Stockpiled Count the user has, Spit Up’s Damage Base is increased by +8. If the user has no Stockpiled count, Spit Up cannot be used.

Name: Strength
Description: You may immediately initiate a Push Maneuver as a Free Action. The Maneuver automatically hits, but you must still make the Opposed Roll.

Name: Splash
Description: Shift Action - The user may make a single Jump, adding +1 to their Long Jump and High Jump values, and gains +2 Evasion until the end of their next turn.

Name: Substitute
Description: The user loses 1/4 of their maximum Hit Points. This Hit Point loss cannot be prevented in any way. The user creates an Illusory Substitute Coat, which has Hit Points equal to 1/4th of the user’s full Hit Points +1. If the user would be hit by a Move or attack, instead the Substitute gets hit. Apply weakness, resistance and stats to the Substitute. The Substitute is immune to Status Afflictions and Status Moves. Moves with the Social or Sonic keywords completely ignore and bypass the Substitute. Once the Substitute has been destroyed, the user may be hit as normal. Substitute cannot be used if the user has less than 1/4 of their full Hit Points.

Name: Swagger
Description: The target’s Attack is raised 2 Combat Stages. Swagger Confuses the target.

Name: Swallow
Description: If the user’s Stockpiled count is 1, they are healed 25% of their full Hit Point value; if their Stockpiled count is 2, they are healed half of their full Hit Point value; if their Stockpiled count is 3, they are healed back to full Hit Points. After using Swallow, the user’s Stockpiled count is set to 0. If the user has no Stockpiled count, Swallow does nothing.

Name: Super Fang
Description: The target loses 1/2 of their current Hit Points.

Name: Sweet Scent
Description: Targets hit by Sweet Scent gain a -2 Penalty to Evasion. (Total Evasion may not be lowered to a negative value.)

Name: Supersonic
Description: The target becomes Confused. On miss, the target suffers a -2 penalty to Accuracy Rolls for one full round.

Name: Swift
Description: Swift cannot Miss.

Name: Swords Dance
Description: The user’s Attack is raised 2 Combat Stages.

Name: Take Down
Description: You may perform a Trip Maneuver against the target as a Free Action.

Name: Tackle
Description: The target is pushed 2 Meters.

Name: Techno Blast
Description: Techno Blast’s Type can be any Type while holding the appropriate Drive item or Plate item.

Name: Tail Slap
Description: None

Name: Teeter Dance
Description: Teeter Dance Confuses all Legal Targets.

Name: Tail Whip
Description: All legal targets have their Defense lowered by 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Thrash
Description: After damage is dealt, the user becomes Enraged and Confused.

Name: Tickle
Description: Lower the target’s Attack 1 Combat Stage and lower the target’s Defense 1 Combat Stage.

Name: Trump Card
Description: Whenever Trump Card is used, the user gains a Trump Count after the attack is resolved. Trump Card’s Damage Base is increased by +2 for each Trump Count.

Name: Transform
Description: The user targets a Pokémon within 10 meters, and assumes the form of the target. It gains all of the user’s Moves, gains its Abilities, copies its weight and height and Capabilities. Transform lasts until the user is switched out, KO’d or until the end of the encounter. The user may choose to end the Transformation on its turn as a free action, regaining its previous Move List. The user’s Stats do not change from using Transform. Transform cannot miss.

Name: Uproar
Description: All Pokémon and Trainers within 5 meters of the user are cured of sleep.

Name: Toxic
Description: The target is Badly Poisoned. If the user is Poison Type, Toxic cannot miss.
